Description, male
(n = 3): Idiosoma small (L/W 549 (584–589)/402) (
Fig. 1
); integument dorso-laterally lined, dorso-medially and ventrally rather granular; posterior dorsal plate relatively large (L/W 164 (176– 184)/140 (159–169)), rounded rectangular-oval, posteriorly wider (
Fig. 2
), anterior dorsal platelets oblique oval (L/W 49 (54–56)/37 (37–44)), one pair of very small knob-shaped sclerites anterior to Dgl–3; glandularia slightly extended, setae of Dgl-4 and -5 larger than all others (
Fig. 2
); lateral eyes, separated on both sides, lying free under the integument, very close lateral to Dgl–2; Cx-I medially closely approached, but separated (
Fig. 1
), postero-lateral margin of Cx-II overlapping Cx-III; medial margin of Cx-III extended by fine secondary sclerotization, medial margin of Cx-IV strongly diverging latero-caudally, with cone-shaped caudal corner (
Fig. 1
), medio- or latero-caudally extended by fine secondary sclerotization (
Fig. 1
); Cxgl-2 fused with Cx-III, Cxgl-4 closely approached to the anterior margin of Cx-III (
Fig. 1
); genital field lying in wide genital bay mainly posterior to coxal field (
Fig. 1
), genital flaps large, anteriorly tapering, caudally broadened (
Fig.1
); acetabula large (L/W 39–49 (44–51)/18–22 (20–22) oval, touching each other, Ac1 slightly distant from anterior margin of genital flaps (
Fig. 1
); anterior genital sclerite small, bowed with medial bump (
Fig. 1
), posterior genital sclerite large, crescent-shaped, broader than genital field, caudal margin fine, irregular (
Fig. 1
); excretory pore without sclerotization; Vgl slightly extended by secondary sclerotization, four small, irregular platelets on a curved line parallel the caudal margin of idiosoma (
Fig. 1
); legs bearing several large setae (several pinnate, distally mostly flatly broadened); claws on leg-I to leg-III well developed with one small dorsal and one larger ventral clawlet (
Fig. 3
), leg-IV-6 distally tapering with one relatively small, slightly pinnate sub-terminal seta (
Fig. 4
); capitulum compact, ventrally straight, no distinct rostrum (
Fig. 5
), palps relatively slender (
Figs 5, 6
), P1 with one small dorsal seta, P2 with one relatively short latero-ventral seta and five to six dorsal setae, ventral margin straight, P3 with two latero-dorsal and two latero-medial fine setae, ventral margin curved, P4 slender, relatively straight, ventro-distally slightly curved ventral setae slightly distal on very weak protrusions (
Figs 5, 6
), chelicera with strong, slightly curved claw (
Fig. 7
).

Female
(n = 8): Posterior dorsal plate nearly rounded (
Fig. 9
); idiosoma larger (L/W 579-736/432-589) (
Fig. 8
); Cx-IV and genital field more elongated than in males; genital flaps straight, anterior genital sclerite larger, more triangular, posterior genital sclerite smaller, bowed with medial bump, not protruding beyond genital field (
Fig. 8
); no significant sexual dimorphism in legs, distal segments of leg-II slightly more elongated than in males (
Fig. 10
); gnathosoma as in male.
